  "body": "The ERC20 Guide page for decimals uses bitwise XOR `^` operator instead of exponentiation operator `**` for decimals demo.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\nThe docs use the XOR operator instead of the exponentiation operator which leads to different results when users try to produce their own implementation.\r\n\r\n**üî¢ Code to reproduce bug**\r\n\r\n```\r\nconstructor(uint256 maxSupply) {\r\n    _totalSupply = maxSupply * (10 ^ decimals());\r\n    balances[msg.sender] = _totalSupply;\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nMints 24,00,000 tokens for 18 decimals and 100,000 maxSupply values. Which should instead be 1e23.\r\n",
